\f1\fs36 What Information We Collect From Users
\f0\b\fs24 \
Location Information
\b0 \
Location information is requested from your mobile device.  Denying Pinsit access to Location information will cause the app to fail to function.  Location information is used to place your posted videos in the correct position on the map and to locate other pins near you.  You can deny Pinsit access to your location information by disabling it on your device's settings or by deleting Pinsit from your device.\
\

\b Phone Number\

\b0 Your phone number is requested before you may post a video.  If you attempt to post a video without verifying your phone number, Pinsit will ask you to verify.  \
\

\b Account Information\

\b0 Upon registering for Pinsit, your username, email address, and signup date are recorded.\
\

\b Post Information\

\b0 We record information about each video that is posted.  This includes your username, video id, posting location, video file, ip-address, phone number, and device information.  \
\

\b Contact Information\

\b0 When you contact Pinsit, we collect any information that you volunteer.\
